<h2>Key to Crassulaceae</h2><a href='http://herbaria4.herb.berkeley.edu/eflora_display.php?tid=109'><h3>View taxon page for Crassulaceae</h3></a><blockquote><h3></h3>
<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#PV1'">1.</a><a name="PV1."> </a> Annual; leaf &lt; 1 cm; flower 1&ndash;5 mm

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#PV2'">2.</a><a name="PV2."> </a> Basal, cauline leaves opposite, bases fused, &plusmn; sheathing; flowers 1 in axils of leaves; petals &lt; 2 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=10872">.....&nbsp;CRASSULA</a> (3)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#PV2.">2'</a><a name="PV2'"> </a> Basal leaves opposite, cauline alternate, bases free, not sheathing; flowers 1 or >= 2 in cyme, terminal; petals 1.3&ndash;5 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=10881">.....&nbsp;SEDELLA</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#PV1.">1'</a><a name="PV1'"> </a> Generally perennial herb to shrub; leaf > 1 cm; flower generally > 10 mm (if annual, flower > 4 mm)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#PV3'">3.</a><a name="PV3."> </a> Subshrub to shrub

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#PV4'">4.</a><a name="PV4."> </a> Leaves alternate

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#PV5'">5.</a><a name="PV5."> </a> Leaves ciliate, rosettes terminal; sepals 7&ndash;11 <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=10870">.....&nbsp;AEONIUM</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#PV5.">5'</a><a name="PV5'"> </a> Leaves not ciliate, rosettes 0; sepals 5 <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=10882">.....&nbsp;SEDUM</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#PV4.">4'</a><a name="PV4'"> </a> Leaves opposite

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#PV6'">6.</a><a name="PV6."> </a> Leaves generally 2&ndash;4 pairs; petals fused, tube >> sepals <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=10871">.....&nbsp;COTYLEDON</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#PV6.">6'</a><a name="PV6'"> </a> Leaves generally > 4 pairs; petals free or &plusmn; fused at base, tube 0 <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=10872">.....&nbsp;CRASSULA</a> (3)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#PV3.">3'</a><a name="PV3'"> </a> Perennial herb (annual or biennial in <I>Sedum radiatum</I>)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#PV7'">7.</a><a name="PV7."> </a> Inflorescences axillary <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=10874">.....&nbsp;DUDLEYA</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#PV7.">7'</a><a name="PV7'"> </a> Inflorescences terminal

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#PV8'">8.</a><a name="PV8."> </a> Sepals, petals generally 5 <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=10882">.....&nbsp;SEDUM</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#PV8.">8'</a><a name="PV8'"> </a> Sepals, petals generally 4

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#PV9'">9.</a><a name="PV9."> </a> Flowers bisexual; stamens = sepals in number <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=10872">.....&nbsp;CRASSULA</a> (3)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#PV9.">9'</a><a name="PV9'"> </a> Flowers &plusmn; unisexual; stamens 2 &times; sepals in number <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=69166">.....&nbsp;RHODIOLA</a></blockquote><P>
